Req. No. 3877 Page 2

1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 21.2 of Title 44, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 As applicable to the procedure for the enlistment, organization,
5 pay, maintenance, equipment, and disciplining of such forces, such
6 compensation shall be in conformity with the law and the rules and
7 regulations governing and pertaining to the Oklahoma National Guard;
8 provided, that the officers and enlisted personnel in the Oklahoma
9 State Guard shall not receive any compensation or monetary
10 allowances from the state except when activated for state active
11 duty, as defined in Section 801 of Title 44 of the Oklahoma
12 Statutes, by order of the Governor. Any full-time state employee
13 who serves in a military capacity shall receive compensation
14 equivalent to the compensation, benefits, entitlements, or other
15 compensation received by a full-time active-duty service member at
16 the same rank and time in grade for the same duration. Compensation
17 received pursuant to this section shall be funded by the Oklahoma
18 National Guard Supplemental Retention Pay Revolving Fund established
19 pursuant to Section 272 of Title 44 of the Oklahoma Statutes or any
20 other funds appropriated.
21 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 44 O.S. 2021, Section 26, as
22 amended by Section 4, Chapter 344, O.S.L. 2025 (44 O.S. Supp. 2025,
23 Section 26), is amended to read as follows:
24
Req. No. 3877 Page 3

1 Section 26. A. The Adjutant General shall be in control of the
2 Military Department of the State of Oklahoma, subordinate only to
3 the Governor. Within the limitations and under the provisions of
4 law, he or she shall supervise and direct the Oklahoma National
5 Guard within the service of the state and when under state control
6 in all of its organization, training and other activities; shall
7 receive and give effect to the orders of the Governor; and shall
8 perform such other military and defense duties, not otherwise
9 assigned by law, as the Governor may prescribe. The Adjutant
10 General shall have the authority to arm members of the state
11 military forces on military installations and other places under the
12 control of the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma with
13 weaponry as the Adjutant General deems necessary to adequately
14 provide for the security of the facilities and their occupants.
15 B. The Adjutant General, when absent from the state, may
16 temporarily delegate any authority vested under this title and any
17 such duties as an agency appointing authority to an Assistant
18 Adjutant General, other state officer or employee within the
19 Military Department of the State of Oklahoma. Such temporary
20 delegations of authority pursuant to this subsection shall be
21 accomplished in writing. The Adjutant General may also promulgate
22 regulations providing for the delegation of any such authority.
23 C. The Adjutant General shall develop, publish and maintain an
24 organizational chart depicting the chain of command between the
Req. No. 3877 Page 4

1 Adju tant General and the major commands of the Oklahoma National
2 Guard. Besides the major commands defined in Section 801 of this
3 title (Article 1), the Adjutant General, in his or her discretion,
4 may designate other military units within the Oklahoma National
5 Guard as major commands.
6 D. The organizational chart required in subsection C of this
7 section shall be updated no less than annually and shall include all
8 enlisted and officer billets assigned to joint forces force
9 headquarters and shall depict all existing command relationships
10 established by the Adjutant General within joint forces force
11 headquarters. The organizational chart required herein shall not be
12 considered a military publication within the meaning of Section 801
13 of this title (Article 1).
14 E. In accordance with all relevant requirements of the United
15 States Army, the United States Air Force or the National Guard
16 Bureau, the Adjutant General shall develop, publish and maintain an
17 enlisted and officer rating scheme for all enlisted and officer
18 billets assigned to joint forces force headquarters. The rating
19 scheme required herein shall not be considered a military
20 publication within the meaning of Section 801 of this title (Article
21 1).
22 F. Pursuant to the rules established by the Adjutant General,
23 the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma is authorized to
