1 2025 , in order to be paid the full amount of such benefit. No
2 member of the Oklahoma National Guard shall be eligible to receive a
3 payment pursuant to the provisions of this section unless the member
4 has completed twenty-five (25) years of military service, which
5 shall include at least five (5) years in the Oklahoma National
6 Guard, and retires as a member of the Oklahoma National Guard. Such
7 member who qualifies for such benefits pursuant to this section
8 shall be deemed a qualifying member.
9 C. The provisions of this section shall not be applicable to
10 any person who retires with an active duty military pension is
11 receiving funds pursuant to 10 U.S.C., Section 12732.
12 D. The amount of the payment shall be determined as follows:
13 1. Determine the amount of retirement the member would receive
14 if the member had reached the age to accrue federal retirement
15 benefits based upon total points accrued;
16 2. If the members of the active duty military retirement system
17 were eligible for a cost-of-living adjustment for the year for which
18 the computation of the payment amount authorized by this section is
19 to be made, the cost-of-living adjustment amount in an annualized
20 form shall be added to the result of the computation in paragraph 1
21 of this subsection each year; and
22 3. The resulting amount shall be paid to the Oklahoma National
23 Guard member in twelve (12) equal monthly amounts with allowance as
24 required for rounding.
