Req. No. 3877 Page 12

1 H. In the event the funds required for full payment to all
2 eligible members pursuant to the provisions of this section are not
3 sufficient, the payments to the eligible members shall be prorated
4 by dividing the total number of eligible members by the total amount
5 of available funds. The resulting quotient shall be multiplied by
6 the payment amount otherwise due to the eligible member and the
7 result of that computation shall be the reduced dollar amount paid
8 to each member for the applicable period. For any period of time
9 during which payments are prorated pursuant to this subsection, the
10 next increment of available funds shall be used to make payments to
11 the eligible members whose payment amounts were prorated to
12 compensate for the reduction made in the prior payment period.
