10 Section 815. ARTICLE 15. Commanding officer’s nonjudicial
11 punishment.
12 A. Except as provided in subsection B of this section, any
13 commanding officer may impose disciplinary punishments for minor
14 offenses arising under the punitive articles of the Oklahoma Uniform
15 Code of Military Justice without the intervention of a court-
16 martial.
17 B. Any commanding officer may limit or withhold the exercise of
18 nonjudicial punishment authority by subordinate commanders,
19 including limiting authority over certain categories of military
