13 M. Whenever nonjudicial punishment is imposed under this
14 section:
15 1. After adjudication and while the punishment is being carried
16 out or while the adjudged punishment is pending before the appellate
17 authority, the commander or officer in charge who imposed the
18 nonjudicial punishment, upon the request of the member officer, may:
19 a. excuse the member officer from attendance at scheduled
20 unit training assemblies, or
21 b. arrange for the member officer to drill on alternate
